CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 22, 1969, pg. 6 reads: "Egyptian Tea - The Daughters and Officers of Sahara Court Nine, gave their annual Egyptian Tea Mar. 9, at the new home of Sahara Mosque on Orr St. Members of the new Egyptian Band are pictured first row, from left to right: Illustrious Commandress Catherine Pickett, Mary Ellen Taylor, Mildred Smart, Natalie Green, Tillie Larkin, Hazel Bradford, Lois Lee Dorsey and Virginia Cohen. Back row: Anna M. Washington, Henriette Forrest, Elfrieda Patterson, and Romaine Moody.  The little girl is Daviea Lynn Taylor. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Daughters and Officers of Sahara Court Nine, first row, from left: Catherine Pickett, Mary Ellen Taylor, Mildred Smart, Natalie Green, Daviea Lynn Taylor, girl; Tillie Larkin, Hazel Bradford, Lois Lee Dorsey, and Virginia Cohen; back row: Anna M. Washington, Henriette Forrest, Elfrieda Patterson, and Romaine Moody, posed in Sahara Mosque for annual Egyptian Tea, Orr Street
